# SerLCD SPI Command Sender

Small AVR C utility for sending a command sequence to a SparkFun SerLCD-style display over SPI.

This snippet was created as a quick hardware recovery/configuration utility while working with a SparkFun SerLCD / OpenLCD-style display. It initializes SPI0 on an AVR DB-style microcontroller and sends a two-byte command sequence:

```c
0x7C
0x0D